text: The Samsø Common List (Danish: Fælleslisten Samsø), formerly The Samsø List (Danish: Samsø-Listen), is a local political party set in Samsø Municipality on the island of Samsø. Inge-Dorthe Larsen is currently representing the party in the municipal council of Samsø Municipality. ==History== In 2001, 7 candidates ran for The Samsø List. The party got two seats in the municipal council in Samsø Municipality, by receiving 16.66% of the votes.kmdvalg.dk Results Samsø Municipality, 2001 In 2005, they lost one of those seats, by going back to 7.4% of the votes. This resulted in a single seat.kmdvalg.dk Results Samsø Municipality, 2005 In 2009, the party received 4.7% of the votes. After this election, "The Samsø List" changed the name to "Fælleslisten Samsø".kmdvalg.dk Results Samsø Municipality, 2009 With four candidates in 2013, Samsø Common List received 10.8% of the votes, resulting in a single seat.kmdvalg.dk Results Samsø Municipality, 2013 ==Election results== === Municipal elections === {|class="wikitable" |- ! rowspan="2"| Date ! rowspan="2"| Votes ! colspan="2"| Seats |- ! # ! ± |- ! 2001 | 482 | | New |- ! 2005 | 191 | | 1 |- ! 2009 | 119 | | 0 |- ! 2013 | 275 | | 0 |} ==References== Category:Political parties in Denmark Category:Political parties with year of establishment missing
